<h1>Step 1</h1>
<p>When a user enters some text in the textbox below and clicks 'Search', the application should show the first 40 Stackoverflow questions, with accepted answers, containing search terms terms in the title, body or tags. Along with the link, you must show:
    <ul>
        <li>question title</li>
        <li>time</li>
        <li>number of responses</li>
        <li>author name</li>
        <li>tags</li>
        <li>avatar image</li>
        <li>accepted answer text, author and avatar</li>
        <li>link to accepted response in stackoverflow site</li>
    </ul></p>
<p><strong>We expect you do this implementation client-side.</strong> You can use whatever client side libraries or frameworks you prefer (knockout, jquery, angular, react...). <strong>We will evaluate code cleanliness and maintainability.</strong> In any case, you have to modify the HomeController and StackExchangeSearch classes. Needless to say, you can add files if necessary, or modify existing ones if you think it's appropriate.</p>
